Binding proteins specific for insulin-like growth factors and uses thereof AbstractBinding proteins, such as antibodies directed to IGF-II with cross-reactivity to IGF-I and uses of such antibodies are described. In particular, fully human monoclonal antibodies directed to the IGF-II with cross-reactivity to IGF-I are disclosed. Also discussed are nucleotide sequences encoding, and amino acid sequences comprising, heavy and light chain immunoglobulin molecules, particularly sequences corresponding to contiguous heavy and light chain sequences spanning the framework regions and/or complementarity determining regions (CDR's), specifically from FR1 through FR4 or CDR1 through CDR3. Claims (
16
)







A fully human isolated antibody, or antigen binding fragment thereof, that preferentially binds to insulin-like growth factor-II (IGF-II) with cross-reactivity to insulin-like growth factor I (IGF-I), wherein said antibody, or antigen binding fragment thereof, comprises three heavy chain complementarity determining regions (HCDR1, HCDR2 and HCDR3) and three light chain complementarity determining regions (LCDR1, LCDR2, and LCDR3) wherein

HCDR1 comprises a sequence at least 90% identical to the amino acid sequence of "Ser Tyr Asp Ile Asn" (SEQ ID NO: 33),

HCDR2 comprises a sequence at least 90% identical to the amino acid sequence of "Trp Met Asn Pro Asn Ser Gly Asn Thr Gly Tyr Ala Gln Lys Phe Gln Gly" (SEQ ID NO: 34);

HCDR3 comprises a sequence at least 90% identical to the amino acid sequence of "Asp Pro Tyr Tyr Tyr Tyr Tyr Gly Met Asp Val" (SEQ ID NO: 35);

LCDR1 comprises a sequence at least 90% identical to the amino acid sequence of "Ser Gly Ser Ser Ser Asn Ile Glu Asn Asn His Val Ser" (SEQ ID NO: 36);

LCDR2 comprises a sequence at least 90% identical to the amino acid sequence of "Asp Asn Asn Lys Arg Pro Ser" (SEQ ID NO: 37); and

LCDR3 comprises a sequence at least 90% identical to the amino acid sequence of "Glu Thr Trp Asp Thr Ser Leu Ser Ala Gly Arg Val" (SEQ ID NO: 38).








The fully human isolated antibody, or antigen binding fragment thereof, of claim 1, wherein the heavy chain CDR1 comprises a sequence at least 95% identical to the sequence of SEQ ID NO: 33, the heavy chain CDR2 comprises a sequence at least 95% identical to the sequence of SEQ ID NO: 34, and the heavy chain CDR3 comprises a sequence at least 95% identical to the sequence of SEQ ID NO: 35.








The fully human isolated antibody, or antigen binding fragment thereof, of claim 1 or 2, wherein the heavy chain CDR1 comprises a sequence at least 99% identical to the sequence of SEQ ID NO: 33, the heavy chain CDR2 comprises a sequence at least 99% identical to the sequence of SEQ ID NO: 34, and the heavy chain CDR3 comprises a sequence at least 99% identical to the sequence of SEQ ID NO: 35.








The fully human isolated antibody, or antigen binding fragment thereof, of any one of claims 1 to 3, wherein the heavy chain CDR1 comprises the sequence of SEQ ID NO: 33, the heavy chain CDR2 comprises the sequence of SEQ ID NO: 34, and the heavy chain CDR3 comprises the sequence of SEQ ID NO: 35.








The fully human isolated antibody, or antigen binding fragment thereof, of any one of claims 1 to 4, wherein the light chain CDR1 comprises a sequence at least 95% identical to the sequence of SEQ ID NO: 36, the light chain CDR2 comprises a sequence at least 95% identical to the sequence of SEQ ID NO: 37, and the light chain CDR3 comprises a sequence at least 95% identical to the sequence of SEQ ID NO: 38.








The fully human isolated antibody, or antigen binding fragment thereof, of any one of claims 1 to 5, wherein the light chain CDR1 comprises a sequence at least 99% identical to the sequence of SEQ ID NO: 36, the light chain CDR2 comprises a sequence at least 99% identical to the sequence of SEQ ID NO: 37, and the light chain CDR3 comprises a sequence at least 99% identical to the sequence of SEQ ID NO: 38.








The fully human isolated antibody, or antigen binding fragment thereof, of any one of claims 1 to 6, wherein the light chain CDR1 comprises the sequence of SEQ ID NO: 36, the light chain CDR2 comprises the sequence of SEQ ID NO: 37, and the light chain CDR3 comprises the sequence of SEQ ID NO: 38.








The antigen binding fragment of any one of claims 1 to 7, wherein said antigen binding fragment is selected from the group consisting of Fab, Fab', F(ab')2 and Fv.








The antibody, or antigen binding fragment, of any one of claims 1 to 8 in a mixture with a pharmaceutically acceptable carrier.








A nucleic acid molecule encoding the antibody, or antigen binding fragment, of any one of claims 1 to 8.








A vector comprising the nucleic acid molecule of claim 10.








An isolated host cell comprising the vector of claim 11.








A method of producing the antibody, or antigen binding fragment thereof, of any one of claims 1 to 8, comprising culturing the host cell of claim 12.








The method of claim 13, wherein the host cell is chosen from: Chinese hamster ovary (CHO) cells, HeLa cells, baby hamster kidney (BHK) cells, monkey kidney cells (COS), human hepatocellular carcinoma cells and human epithelial kidney 293 cells.








An antibody, or antigen binding fragment, of any one of claims 1 to 8 for treating a malignant tumor in a mammal.








